SUMMARY:Sounds of Spring: Frog Calls
DESCRIPTION:Are you curious about the frogs that live around us? Want to learn about frog ecology\, and how to identify local frogs by sound? Join us in the evening for a casual walk down to the pond\, where we will listen for frogs\, practice our frog call identification\, and record observations to help researchers better understand frog populations and ecology in the Piedmont.\n\nThis program is free and open to everyone ages 8+\, but registration is required. We will meet by the kiosk before walking as a group across the prairie to the pond. Dress for the weather and bring water.\nRegister here
URL:https://naturalsciences.org/calendar/event/sounds-of-spring-frog-calls/
