SUMMARY:Science Trivia
DESCRIPTION:What’s cooler than absolute zero? The answer is Science Trivia night at NCMNS! \nQuestions feature a mix of science facts\, current news\, pop culture and scientific discoveries. Held in the Daily Planet Cafe the first Thursday of each month\, this is a great opportunity to mingle with friends\, compete for prizes and bragging rights\, and perhaps even learn something cool. \nThe Museum closes at 5 PM; the Daily Planet Cafe will remain open.
URL:https://naturalsciences.org/calendar/event/science-trivia-3/2026-04-02/
LOCATION:Downtown Raleigh\, 11 West Jones Street\, Raleigh\, NC\, 27601\, United States
CATEGORIES:Adults,Daily Planet Cafe,General Events,Science Cafes,Teens,Trivia
