SUMMARY:The Key to Identification
DESCRIPTION:How do you tell the difference between a tiger and a leopard? Or a dragonfly and a butterfly? Come learn about how scientists tell organisms apart using a tool called a dichotomous key – and how to make your own! \nThis program is for ages 8+ and will be conducted entirely outdoors.  Please dress for the weather\, wear closed toed shoes\, and bring water.  We will meet in the Outdoor Classroom\, a 3-5 minute walk down the gravel road from the parking lot.
URL:https://naturalsciences.org/calendar/event/the-key-to-identification/
LOCATION:Prairie Ridge\, 1671 Gold Star Drive\, Raleigh\, NC\, 27607\, United States
CATEGORIES:Adults,Children,Citizen Science,K-12 Students,Outdoor Experiences,Teens,Walk-up Programs
